`OverlayPortal.overlayChildLayoutBuilder` can throw a framework assertion when a shown portal is reactivated while a `LayoutBuilder` subtree is being laid out.

I can reproduce this in a plain Flutter app with no router and no application-specific overlay abstraction. The sample has a shown `OverlayPortal` under a `GlobalKey`. Tapping a button moves that portal target from one stable parent slot to another inside a `LayoutBuilder`.

