## Describe the bug

`ImageReaderSurfaceProducer.PerImageReader.onImageAvailableListener` calls `scheduleEngineFrame()` (via `onImage()`) without first checking `flutterJNI.isAttached()`. The legacy `SurfaceTextureRegistryEntry` path guards this same call at line 345:

```java
// SurfaceTextureRegistryEntry.onFrameListener (line 343–354) — has the guard:
if (released || !flutterJNI.isAttached()) {
    return;
}
scheduleEngineFrame();
```

```java
// ImageReaderSurfaceProducer.PerImageReader.onImageAvailableListener (line 529–545) — missing the guard:
if (released || closed) {   // <-- no isAttached() check
    image.close();
    return;
}
onImage(r, image);          // → scheduleEngineFrame() at line 660
```

